# Viewing and creating Hidder files 
1. Hidder files are used to store configuration settings and system - related data.
2. They are typically hidden to prevent accidenatal changes or deletions by users.
3. Viewing and creating hidden files allows users to manage and cuztomize system behavior when needed.









### Help commands
1. command --help  (eg: ls --help)
2. man command (eg: man ls)
3. info command 